1.title: Blacklisted
1.plot: Eddie and Chad are best friends and background actors. When they get a text from their boss, Harry Kuntz of Kuntz Calling Services, they go in expecting the worse. Once in the office, they think they're in the clear until the phone rings.

2.title: Moguls
2.plot: After Eddie and Chad get canned by Kuntz, they go get Chinese food. Eddie hashes up a plan to start their own call service even though Chad has his reservations. That's until Crystal shows up wanting to rekindle their old relationship.

imdb.plot outline: Eddie and Chad are two lifelong friends who "work" as extras on sets for a living in LA. Whenever they're on set, Eddie takes the advantage to hustle people and sells random stuff (weed, fake Rolex watches, etc.) while Chad's only purpose is to meet girls. The show starts out as Eddie and Chad get fired from a film set for "lack of professionalism" and get "blacklisted" given the fact that it's not the first time they've caused trouble on set. Being a true "businessman", Eddie suggests that they open their own extras calling services and not "wait around for a handout." As Eddie books the first gig for their "company" which is an unknown indie film, Chad is trying to get people for their "roster." Chad couldn't book any talents since their company is not legally formed. He then tries to get his friends and relatives to help them out with the "indie" film shoot, which turns out to be something unexpected.
